description:
This follow-up to Heavens to Betsy is a delightful faith-based comedy with a poignant message about honoring God, no matter what the cost.

"Author Betsy Simon (Karen Lesiewicz) finally finds career success when her new novel, Heavens to Betsy, is published. The book tells the story of a young woman who is transported to an alternate universe where all the prayers she ever prayed are answered all at once. Following advice from her agent (Ruth Kaufman), she tells the public that the book is a work of fiction. After talking with Pastor John (Jim O'Heir from TV's ""Parks and Recreation"") Betsy cannot continue to lie, so she risks her career and her credibility when she claims that the events portrayed in the book actually happened to her! Now she must defend her faith before a skeptical world when she agrees to do a high-profile interview with Tandum Dackery (Gary Gow), a self-serving media personality who is bent on exposing Betsy as a fraud.

Director: Robert Alaniz
Writer: Robert Alaniz
Starring: Karen Lesiewicz, Jim O'Heir, Steve Parks
